# help/en/overview.ftl — Cloud White Theme help texts (English)

help-cloud-white-title = Cloud White Theme

help-cloud-white-body =
    Cloud White is the FreeSynergy light theme — clean, bright, and designed for
    well-lit environments and users who prefer light mode. It uses white and light
    gray backgrounds with ocean blue accents and dark charcoal text.

    Color palette:
    - Background: bright white (#f8fafc, #ffffff) and very light gray
    - Accent: ocean blue (#0077b6) for interactive elements
    - Text: dark charcoal (#0f172a) for primary text, medium slate for secondary
    - Status: green for success, amber for warnings, red for errors — all in
      saturated variants suitable for light backgrounds

    Cloud White is designed for high readability in daylight. The low background
    luminance makes content and status indicators easy to distinguish.

help-cloud-white-apply-title = Applying the Theme

help-cloud-white-apply-body =
    1. Open Desktop Settings > Appearance > Theme.
    2. Select "Cloud White" from the theme list.
    3. Click Apply. Changes take effect immediately — no logout required.

    Tip: If your environment switches between indoor and outdoor use, consider
    switching to Midnight Blue or Nordic Dark in darker environments. The theme
    change takes effect instantly with no session restart.
